    <briefdescription>
<para>Detection-theory utilities for the amplitude-ratio test statistic. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The doppler detector forms the test statistic:</para>
<para>test_stat = peak_mag / noise_est</para>
<para>With M-point coherent integration (dwell = M) and per-sample amplitude SNR <computeroutput>snr</computeroutput> (signal amplitude / noise amplitude, linear):</para>
<para>Under H0 (noise only): test_stat ~ Rayleigh(1) Under H1 (signal+noise): test_stat ~ Rice(a, 1), a = sqrt(2*M) * snr</para>
<para>False-alarm probability (threshold-only, M-independent):</para>
<para>Pfa = exp(-eta^2/2) =&gt; eta = sqrt(-2 ln Pfa) (exact)</para>
<para>Detection probability:</para>
<para>Pd = Q_1(a, eta) (Marcum Q function, order 1)</para>
<para>All functions are stateless and thread-safe. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
